@aeickho merge as-is for now and I will test my idea in my repo.
Currently we use travis-cv to test for OS X and Linux. To be able to test for Windows, I have added appveyor.yml so that the same tests can be performed.
The build commands (make all; make clean; etc) are the same for all platforms and both CI arrangements. My idea is to add the build commands to a separate script file that gets called by both travis-ci and appveyor yml files. That way, if we add more tests in the future, we only have to edit the one file.

