@KD4Z : Thanks for the extra details!
Given that my touching the curl invocation is unrelated to the purpose of this PR (improving ci to catch warnings before they get into master), can we split this off into another PR (or maybe an issue)?  I'd be willing to work on it, including the work to pull the curl flags into a single location.
That approach would also give a dedicated place to hash out what the right timeout and retry ought to be.

Seems to be, though I can't use the arm-none-eabi-* ports since they don't do multilib and use soft float.  I also need a weird hack to set the USB config (looks like a problem in the FreeBSD USB stack).  If you're documenting it somewhere, I added the following to /etc/devd.conf:
# Tytera MD-390 and related radios
notify 200 {
        match "system"          "USB";
        match "subsystem"       "DEVICE";
        match "type"            "ATTACH";
        match "vendor"          "0x0483";
        match "product"         "0xdf11";
        action "/usr/sbin/chown root:wheel /dev/$cdev && /bin/chmod 0660 /dev/$cdev && usbconfig -d $cdev set_config 0";
};

That will get the tools working, but actually building the firmware is a bit trickier involving building a working cross-toolchain.
I haven't done much besides dumping everything, doing the firmware and the userdb.  We're mostly just using the md380-dfu for our work over at /WD1CKS/firm-tyt (and it works great).

